official_title: A bill to direct the Secretary of the Interior to convey certain land under the jurisdiction of the Bureau of Land Management in Washakie County and Big Horn County, Wyoming, to the Westside Irrigation District, Wyoming, and for other purposes.

summary.text: Directs the Secretary of the Interior, acting through the Director of the Bureau of Land Management, on completion of an environmental analysis, to convey to the Westside Irrigation District, Wyoming, such portions of specified Federal land (excluding mineral interest) in Big Horn County and Washakie County, Wyoming, as such District enters into an agreement with the Secretary to purchase. Requires the proceeds of such land sale to be deposited in a special account in the Treasury and to be available to the Secretary for the acquisition of land and interests in the Worland District of the Bureau in Wyoming that will benefit public recreation, public access, fish and wildlife habitat, or cultural resources.
